{
  "texts": [
    "There are several ways to categorize these methods.",
    "First, a model-based method learns a model from data to make the prediction, while a signal-based metric does not require learning such a model.",
    "Second, an intrusive (or double-ended) method requires a reference signal for comparison, and a non-intrusive, (or reference-free, single-ended) method does not require a reference.",
    "Difficulties in automatic evaluation of synthetic speechObjective evaluation of synthesized speech is expected to be difficult for several reasons.",
    "First of all, there is the so-called \"one-to-many\" problem -for any given condition (text, style, environment, etc."
